DE  Accessory Sec system for serine-rich glycoprotein transport
TP  SYSTEM
AU  Haft DH
TH  0
RN  [1]
RM  15901716
RT  Two additional components of the accessory sec system mediating export
RT  of the Streptococcus gordonii platelet-binding protein GspB.
RA  Takamatsu D, Bensing BA, Sullam PM;
RL  J Bacteriol. 2005;187:3878-3883.
RN  [2]
RM  18621893
RT  Characterization of the accessory Sec system of Staphylococcus aureus.
RA  Siboo IR, Chaffin DO, Rubens CE, Sullam PM;
RL  J Bacteriol. 2008;190:6188-6196.
CC  A number of Gram-positive pathogens express serine-rich glycoproteins
CC  such as the platelet-binding glycoprotein GspB of Streptococcus
CC  gordonii. At least 5 core proteins contribute to the export of these
CC  proteins, including SecY2 and SecA2, homologs respectively of the SecY
CC  and SecA proteins of the Sec system. Additional proteins are required
CC  for glycosylation rather than export.
**  SecY2, Asp1, Asp2, Asp3, and SecA2 should all be transport not
**  glycosylation. Important examples of the target serine-rich proteins
**  include SAG_1462, SP_1772, SACOL2676. Look at all species with paralog
**  to SecA (TIGR00963), and species with putative TIGR03715 signal
**  peptide. TIGR04224 hits too narrowly (just Strep).
--
